        <fullName>Record_Summary_and_History_16jak000001hGXB</fullName>
        <canEscalate>false</canEscalate>
        <description>This topic handles requests where the sales rep wants a summary, recap, history, or recent activity for a specific Doctor (Person Account) or Facility (Business Account / hospital / clinic). Trigger this topic for phrases like: &quot;tell me about Dr. X&quot;, &quot;what&apos;s my history with Y Hospital&quot;, &quot;recent visits to Apollo&quot;, &quot;how much have I spent on Dr. Z&quot;, &quot;recap of my last visit with...&quot;, &quot;summary for Dr. ...&quot;, &quot;show me everything for ...&quot;, &quot;what have I done with...&quot;, &quot;my activity with ...&quot;. This topic does NOT create new records — it only reads and summarizes existing Visits, Tasks, Expenses, and Affiliations linked to the matched record.</description>
        <developerName>Record_Summary_and_History_16jak000001hGXB</developerName>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>The user wants a summary about a specific Doctor or Facility.
Resolve which one before invoking Get Record Summary.


STEP 1 — Extract the subject from the user&apos;s request:

   - subjectName = the doctor or facility name they mentioned.
                   Strip salutations (Dr., Mr., Ms., Prof.).
   - subjectKind = &quot;Doctor&quot; if they used a person name with
                   salutation, OR if they referred to a person
                   (&quot;Dr. X&quot;, &quot;Mehta&quot;, &quot;with Sharma&quot;).
                   &quot;Facility&quot; if the mention contains hospital
                   keywords (Hospital, Clinic, Medical Center,
                   etc.) or sounds like a place name (e.g.,
                   &quot;Apollo&quot;, &quot;Manipal&quot;, &quot;City Care&quot;).
                   When ambiguous, default to &quot;Doctor&quot; first
                   — fall back to &quot;Facility&quot; if the Doctor
                   lookup returns NotFound.


STEP 2 — Invoke Query Records to resolve the subject&apos;s recordId:

   Call &quot;Query Records&quot; with:
       objectType   = subjectKind  (&quot;Doctor&quot; or &quot;Facility&quot;)
       searchName   = subjectName

   For Doctor lookups, also pass searchFacility and searchPhone
   IF the user mentioned a facility or phone number alongside
   the doctor name. Never concatenate facility/phone into
   searchName.


STEP 3 — Handle Query Records status:

   - status = &quot;NotFound&quot; with subjectKind = &quot;Doctor&quot;:
        Try again with subjectKind = &quot;Facility&quot; (fallback).
        If still NotFound: tell the user no matching record was
        found and ask for a corrected spelling. STOP.

   - status = &quot;NotFound&quot; with subjectKind = &quot;Facility&quot;:
        Tell the user no matching record was found and ask for a
        corrected spelling. STOP.

   - status = &quot;TooMany&quot;:
        Ask the user for a more specific detail (full name,
        facility, phone, city). STOP and wait. RE-INVOKE with
        merged inputs on next turn.

   - status = &quot;Success&quot; with matchCount = 1:
        AUTO-RESOLVE SILENTLY using records[0].recordId as
        subjectRecordId. Proceed to Instruction 3.

   - status = &quot;Success&quot; with matchCount &gt; 1:
        Present a numbered list with displayLabel as-is. Ask
        &quot;Reply with the number.&quot; Map reply to recordId, then
        proceed.

   - status = &quot;Error&quot;:
        Surface errorMessage and stop.</description>
            <developerName>instruction_0_1777795500125</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>instruction_0_1777795500125</masterLabel>
