        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>Build a clean, structured summary using ONLY plain text
formatting that works on both Lightning chat and WhatsApp.

ALLOWED formatting:
   - Plain text and newlines
   - Bullets with &quot;-&quot; or numbered lists &quot;1.&quot; &quot;2.&quot;
   - Single asterisks for emphasis: *bold word*

NOT ALLOWED (will look broken on WhatsApp):
   - Markdown headers (#, ##)
   - Tables (| col | col |)
   - Hyperlinks like [text](url) — use plain URLs only
   - Indentation with tabs or multiple spaces
   - Inline images, emoji art


Format template (omit any section where the count is zero):

   *&lt;recordName&gt;* — &lt;recordDetail&gt;
   Window: &lt;human-readable from the timeWindowApplied&gt;

   Affiliations: &lt;affiliationCount&gt;
   &lt;affiliationNames&gt;

   Visits: &lt;visitTotalCount&gt; total
   Last on: &lt;visitLastDate formatted DD/MM/YYYY&gt;
   Recent:
   - &lt;visit line 1&gt;
   - &lt;visit line 2&gt;
   ... (up to 10)

   Tasks: &lt;taskTotalCount&gt; total, &lt;taskOpenCount&gt; open
   - &lt;task line 1&gt;
   - &lt;task line 2&gt;
   ... (up to 10)

   Expenses: &lt;expenseTotalCount&gt; total, Rs. &lt;expenseTotalSpend&gt;
   - &lt;expense line 1&gt;
   - &lt;expense line 2&gt;
   ... (up to 10)


List output rules (CRITICAL — do not skip):
   - For Recent visits: list ALL entries from visitTopRecords as
     returned by the action. Do NOT truncate to fewer than what
     the action returned.
   - For Tasks: list ALL entries from taskTopRecords. Do NOT
     truncate.
   - For Expenses: list ALL entries from expenseTopRecords. Do
     NOT truncate.
   - The action already caps each list at 10 maximum, so showing
     all of them is safe.


Date formatting:
   - Use DD/MM/YYYY format consistently across the entire
     response (header dates and line items must match).
   - The action&apos;s formatted line entries already follow this
     format — use them verbatim.
   - For visitLastDate, fromDate, or any other Date output,
     format as DD/MM/YYYY in your reply.


Window label:
   - Render the timeWindowApplied as a clean, human-readable
     phrase. Do NOT append the year, dates, or extra context
     in parentheses.
   - Examples: &quot;This Year&quot;, &quot;All Time&quot;, &quot;Last 30 Days&quot;,
     &quot;This Quarter&quot;, &quot;Last 7 Days&quot;, &quot;Last Month&quot;.
   - For CUSTOM_DAYS, render as &quot;Last &lt;N&gt; Days&quot;.


Currency formatting:
   - Always use &quot;Rs. &lt;amount&gt;&quot; — NEVER use the rupee symbol,
     &quot;INR&quot;, or &quot;$&quot; anywhere in YOUR generated text.
   - For expenseTotalSpend, output as &quot;Rs. 8000&quot; — no comma,
     no decimal.
   - For line items returned by the action (visitTopRecords,
     taskTopRecords, expenseTopRecords), use them verbatim
     even if they contain a rupee symbol from the original
     visit notes / transcript — that is real data, do not edit.


Section omission rules (ABSOLUTE — strictest interpretation):

   These rules treat &quot;omit&quot; literally — the section must not
   exist in the reply. Do NOT downgrade a zero count to phrases
   like &quot;None recorded&quot;, &quot;No expenses&quot;, &quot;Nothing to show&quot;,
   &quot;0 total&quot;, &quot;Rs. 0&quot; — those are violations.

   - If affiliationCount = 0:
        - DO NOT print &quot;Affiliations:&quot; anywhere.
        - DO NOT print &quot;None&quot;, &quot;No affiliations&quot;, or &quot;0&quot;.
        - The Affiliations block must be COMPLETELY ABSENT from
          the reply — as if the section never existed.

   - If visitTotalCount = 0:
        - DO NOT print &quot;Visits:&quot; anywhere.
        - DO NOT print &quot;Last on:&quot;.
        - DO NOT print &quot;Recent:&quot;.
        - DO NOT print &quot;None&quot;, &quot;No visits&quot;, &quot;0 total&quot;.
        - The Visits block must be COMPLETELY ABSENT from the
          reply.

   - If taskTotalCount = 0:
        - DO NOT print &quot;Tasks:&quot; anywhere.
        - DO NOT print &quot;None&quot;, &quot;No tasks&quot;, &quot;0 total, 0 open&quot;.
        - The Tasks block must be COMPLETELY ABSENT from the
          reply.

   - If expenseTotalCount = 0:
        - DO NOT print &quot;Expenses:&quot; anywhere.
        - DO NOT print &quot;None recorded&quot;, &quot;No expenses&quot;, &quot;Rs. 0&quot;,
          &quot;0 total&quot;, or any variation.
        - The Expenses block must be COMPLETELY ABSENT from the
          reply.

   This omission rule applies to BOTH full summaries (this
   instruction) AND quantitative answers (Instruction 6).

   If the user explicitly asked about a section whose count
   is 0 (e.g. &quot;how many open tasks for X?&quot; with taskOpenCount
   = 0), reply with a single short sentence acknowledging
   that nothing exists — but do NOT use the structured block
   format. Example: &quot;You have no open tasks for Dr. Mehta.&quot;


If ALL four sections are empty (no affiliations, visits, tasks,
or expenses):
   Reply: &quot;I have no records for &lt;recordName&gt; in the selected
   time window (&lt;timeWindowApplied&gt;). Try a wider window like
   &apos;all time&apos; or &apos;this year&apos;.&quot;


Length cap:
   The response should fit within ~25 lines on WhatsApp.
   If visit notes or task descriptions are long, the action&apos;s
   formatted lines are already truncated to 120 characters —
   don&apos;t expand them.</description>
            <developerName>instruction_3_1777795500125</developerName>
