        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>If the user asked a specific quantitative question rather than a
general summary, lead with the direct answer FIRST and keep the
response BRIEF. Do NOT dump the full list — the user asked
&quot;how many&quot; or &quot;how much&quot;, not &quot;show me everything&quot;.


Brevity rules:
   - Lead with the direct numeric answer in the first sentence.
   - Provide AT MOST 1-2 supporting line items, not the full
     visitTopRecords / taskTopRecords / expenseTopRecords list.
   - If the user wants more detail, they will ask a follow-up.
   - Do NOT include sections (Affiliations, etc.) that the user
     did not ask about.
   - Do NOT include the *&lt;recordName&gt;* header — answer
     conversationally.


Section omission still applies:
   - If the answered section&apos;s count = 0, do NOT mention zero.
     Instead reply with a short line like:
        &quot;You have no visits with Dr. &lt;name&gt; in the selected
        time window.&quot;


Examples:

   User: &quot;How many visits did I have this year with Dr. Sharma?&quot;
   Reply: &quot;You had &lt;visitTotalCount&gt; visits with Dr. Sharma this
   year. Last on &lt;visitLastDate formatted DD/MM/YYYY&gt;.&quot;

   User: &quot;How much have I spent on Dr. Mehta?&quot;
   Reply: &quot;You&apos;ve spent Rs. &lt;expenseTotalSpend&gt; across
   &lt;expenseTotalCount&gt; expenses for Dr. Mehta this year.&quot;

   User: &quot;When did I last visit Apollo Hospital?&quot;
   Reply: &quot;Your last visit to Apollo Hospital was on
   &lt;visitLastDate&gt;. &lt;visit line 1&gt;&quot;

   User: &quot;How many open tasks for Dr. Mehta?&quot;
   Reply: &quot;You have &lt;taskOpenCount&gt; open tasks for Dr. Mehta out
   of &lt;taskTotalCount&gt; total.&quot;


When NOT to apply this rule:
   - User asks for a general summary, recap, history, or &quot;tell
     me about&quot; — that&apos;s Instruction 5 (full format).
   - User asks &quot;show me my visits with X&quot; — list-style request,
     use full format from Instruction 5.</description>
            <developerName>instruction_4_1777795500125</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
